h2. üèÜ Complete Example: Before vs After

h3. ‚ùå BEFORE: Poorly Written Ticket

{panel:title=MSTECH-123: Fix login|borderColor=#DE350B}
**Summary:** Fix login

**Description:** Users can't login sometimes

**Priority:** Medium

**Assignee:** Unassigned

**Labels:** None

**Acceptance Criteria:** Make login work
{panel}

h3. ‚úÖ AFTER: Well-Written Ticket  

{panel:title=MSTECH-123: User Authentication: Secure Login with Multi-Factor Authentication|borderColor=#36B37E}
**Summary:** User Authentication: Secure Login with Multi-Factor Authentication

**Description:** Implement comprehensive user authentication system with enhanced security features and improved user experience. Currently, users experience intermittent login failures and there are security concerns about single-factor authentication.

**User Story:**
* **As a** registered user accessing the application
* **When** I am logging into the application from my browser  
* **I want to** securely authenticate and access my personal dashboard
* **So I can** safely manage my personal information and account settings
* **So that** my data remains protected from unauthorized access and I feel confident using the platform

**Acceptance Criteria:**
```
GIVEN a registered user with valid credentials
WHEN they attempt to log in
THEN they should be able to authenticate successfully

Acceptance Criteria:
- [ ] User can enter username and password on login form
- [ ] System validates credentials against secure database  
- [ ] Multi-factor authentication is enforced for all users
- [ ] Failed login attempts are logged and rate-limited
- [ ] Successful login redirects to personalized dashboard
- [ ] Session management follows security best practices (30min timeout)
- [ ] Password reset functionality is available via email
- [ ] Account lockout after 5 failed attempts within 15 minutes
- [ ] Login works across all supported browsers (Chrome, Firefox, Safari, Edge)
- [ ] Mobile-responsive login interface
- [ ] Error messages are user-friendly and don't reveal security details
```

**Priority:** High (affects user access and security)

**Assignee:** security.team.lead

**Labels:** security, user-experience, authentication, high-priority

**Components:** Frontend, Backend, Security

**Epic:** User Security Enhancement Initiative
{panel}

